title: The Rat Pack.Live and Swingin.DVDrip.XviD
description: Hey, pallies, it&#039;s the only known filmed Rat Pack concert from the 1960s -- a 90-minute show from the Kiel Opera House in St. Louis. Backed by a 32-year-old Quincy Jones conducting the Count Basie Orchestra, Frank, Dean and Sammy -- drinks and cigarettes firmly in hand -- croon such timeless classics as "Luck Be a Lady," "Everybody Loves Somebody" and "One for My Baby." Special guest Johnny Carson is on hand to lend some laughs, too.
